# Development Guidelines

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 13+ with App Router
- TypeScript for type safety
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- React Server Components by default

## Development Workflow
1. Use TypeScript for all new code
2. Follow the component structure in [components-guide.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/components-guide.mdc)
3. Follow the app structure in [app-structure.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/app-structure.mdc)

## Code Style
1. Use functional components with TypeScript
2. Implement proper prop types for all components
3. Use Tailwind CSS for styling
4. Follow the existing naming conventions
5. Keep components small and focused
6. Use custom hooks for complex logic

## Performance Guidelines
1. Use React Server Components where possible
2. Implement proper loading states
3. Optimize images and assets
4. Use proper caching strategies
5. Implement error boundaries

## Testing
1. Write tests for critical functionality
2. Test both client and server components
3. Use proper mocking strategies
4. Follow the testing best practices

## Documentation
1. Document complex logic
2. Add JSDoc comments for functions
3. Keep README files up to date
4. Document any non-obvious implementation details
